%N A395956 Denominator of the n-th moment of the probability distribution of distances from the center of a unit disk to a line passing through two points independently and uniformly selected at random in the disk, divided by Pi if n is odd.
%C A395956 The moments of the probability distributed function f(x) = (16/(3*Pi))*(1-x^2)^(3/2) for 0 <= x <= 1, and 0 otherwise.
%D A395956 A. M. Mathai, An Introduction to Geometrical Probability: Distributional Aspects with Applications, Amsterdam: Gordon and Breach, 1999, p. 205, eq. (2.3.66).
%H A395956 Amiram Eldar, <a href="/A395956/b395956.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000</a>
%e A395956 Fractions begin with 1, 16/(15*Pi), 1/6, 32/(105*Pi), 1/16, 128/(945*Pi), 1/32, 256/(3465*Pi), 7/384, 2048/(45045*Pi), 3/256, 4096/(135135*Pi), ...
%t A395956 a[n_] := Denominator[2/Sqrt[Pi]*Gamma[(n + 1)/2]/Gamma[n/2 + 3]] /. Pi -> 1; Array[a, 33, 0]
%o A395956 (PARI) gamma_my(n) = if(denominator(n) == 1, (n-1)!, my(m = n - 1/2); (2*m)! / (4^m * m!)); \\ gamma for integers, gamma(n)/sqrt(Pi) for half-integers
%o A395956 a(n) = denominator(2 * gamma_my((n + 1)/2) / gamma_my(n/2 + 3));
%Y A395956 Cf. A395953, A395954, A395955 (numerators).
%K A395956 nonn,frac,easy,new
%O A395956 0,2
%A A395956 _Amiram Eldar_, May 12 2026
